title: Connecting the Dots | New tools for space qualification
summary: Technology advances and novel businesses are opening up new ways to qualify materials in space. To avoid jeopardizing mission success, manufacturers rigorously test and validate novel materials before using their potentially performance-improving capabilities on customer satellites.

title: Op-Ed: Setting Up Camp, an Exploration of Artemis
summary: After decades of dreaming, We Are Going! The rockets are flying, crews are in training, and the landers are under contract. Artemis will put the first woman and first person of color on the Moon by the end of this decade… But then what? A plan is slowly coming together. NASA along with its commercial and international partners intends to do so much more than flags and footprints. That next landing will be the start of a sustained campaign on the Lunar surface, one that will open up the Moon as a new frontier for international scientific collaboration and where we learn what we need to go to Mars.

title: Intuitive Machines stock jumps in wild trading after moon landing
summary: Shares of Intuitive Machines jumped in trading on Friday after the company’s successful first moon landing.

title: China launches classified military satellite towards geostationary belt
summary: China launched the TJS-11classified satellite early Friday as the country continues to build its geostationary capabilities.

title: Launch Roundup: SpaceX to launch two Starlink missions; China to launch Chang Zheng 5
summary: A brand new week of spaceflight is approaching with SpaceX preparing to launch two Starlink missions, China getting ready to send two payloads to orbit, including one on the powerful Chang Zheng 5 (CZ-5) rocket, and Roscosmos preparing to launch Russian-built satellites to orbit atop Soyuz.

title: A little US company makes history by landing on the Moon
Intuitive Machines lands on the moon
summary: A robotic lander developed by Intuitive Machines landed safely on the moon Feb. 22, becoming the first privately developed spacecraft to touch down on the moon and the first American spacecraft to do so in more than half a century.

title: Avanti to integrate Telesat Lightspeed LEO broadband services
summary: British satellite broadband operator Avanti Communications announced plans Feb. 22 to integrate the low Earth orbit services Canada’s Telesat aims to bring online in 2027 with its regional geostationary network.

title: NGA goes big on commercial satellite data with $290 million ‘Luno’ program
summary: The National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency seeks to leverage commercial satellite imagery and data analytics to enhance its global monitoring capabilities
